<HEADLINE> Truluck Captures Salvator Mile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OCEANPORT, N.J. (AP) -- Truluck took the lead around the final  
turn and went on to a three-length victory over favored Rock and 
Roll in the $150,000 Salvator Mile Handicap at Monmouth Park on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Elliott Walden-trained colt paid $4.80, $2.40 and $2.10 and  
earned $80,000 in winning for the second time in eight starts. 
</P>
<P>
	Rock and Roll returned $2.40 and $2.10, while Siftaway was $2.10  
to show. 
</P>
<P>
	``The first thing I thought when I got on this horse was he was  
Godzilla, and he's the fastest Godzilla I've ever seen,'' jockey 
Joe Bravo said. ``I know Rock and Roll is a good horse and I knew 
once I got alongside of him I wanted to pass him quickly and that's 
how it worked out. My horse finished full of steam.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In the $75,000 Longfellow Stakes, favored My Jeff's Mombo  
($3.60) scored his fourth straight win of the meet, beating Loaded 
Gun by a head. 
</P>
<P>
	Let ($6) rallied strongly under Stewart Elliott to take the  
$70,000 Personal Ensign Stakes by a neck over Sweet Misty. 
</P>
<P>
	In the $70,000 Omnibus Stakes on the turf, Natalie Too came on  
late to score a 1 1/4-length victory over Red Royal for her third 
stakes win of the meet. Bravo rode the D. Wayne Lukas-trained mare, 
who paid $5.20. 
  	   	
</P>
