<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Says Prince Was Winning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHAPPAQUA, N.Y. (AP) -- With his week of golf and socializing on  
Martha's Vineyard, Mass., behind him, President Clinton offered an 
update Saturday on his friendly wager with the duke of York. 
</P>
<P>
	``I had to pay him four dollars,'' Clinton said of Britain's  
Prince Andrew. 
</P>
<P>
	The prince was winning when their party was rained off the  
course on the 15th hole Friday, Clinton said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was catching up,'' the president told reporters aboard Air  
Force One on Saturday, after he left the resort island for a 
weekend of fund raising for Democrats on New York's Long Island. 
The Clintons also squeezed in a little house-hunting in nearby 
Westchester County, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
	The $4 was cheap by comparison to the wager Clinton described at  
the start of the round Friday. He jokingly told reporters then that 
if he lost he had promised to return Martha's Vineyard to the duchy 
of York, which controlled the island in the 17th century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
