<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sayarshan Wins Del Mar Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Sayarshan overtook 19-1 longshot Dancing  
Place in the final sixteenth of a mile Saturday to win the $250,000 
Del Mar Handicap by three-quarters of a length before a crowd of 
18,758. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Brice Blanc and carrying 115 pounds, Sayarshan covered  
1 3/8 miles on turf in 2:14 1-5 and paid $14, $8 and $4.20. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was the fourth in nine lifetime starts for Sayarshan  
and was worth $150,000, increasing the career earnings of the 
4-year-old French-bred son of Darshaan to $338,920. 
</P>
<P>
	Sayarshan won the Golden Gate Handicap in his American debut on  
June 19, but finished eighth in the Sunset Handicap at Hollywood 
Park on July 18. 
</P>
<P>
	Dancing Place, ridden by David Flores and carrying 116 pounds,  
crossed the finish line four lengths in front of 11-10 favorite 
Ladies Din and returned $13.20 and $5.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Ladies Din, ridden by Corey Nakatani and carrying high weight of  
120 pounds, was 1 1/2 lengths ahead of Go at the wire and paid $2.40 
to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Following Go across the finish line in the 60th running of the  
race for 3-year-olds and up were Sestino, Foggy Day, Star 
Performance and Innamorato. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
