<HEADLINE> Lines of Beauty Wins at Ellis Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HENDERSON, Ky. (AP) -- Lines of Beauty took the lead from the  
start and held off a late challenge from Roza Robata to win by a 
neck in the $200,000 Gardenia Stakes on Saturday at Ellis Park. 
</P>
<P>
	The 4-year-old, with jockey Francisco Torres, held a comfortable  
lead midway on the far turn until Roza Robata quickly closed and 
pulled beside her. The two ran side by side for an eighth of a mile 
before Lines of Beauty drew away to win the mile-and-an-eighth 
race. 
</P>
<P>
	Castle Blaze finished six lengths behind in third place in the  
field of 10 fillies and mares. 
</P>
<P>
	Lines of Beauty, trained by Randy Martin, covered the distance  
in 1:49 3-5 and paid $24.40, $11.20 and $7.60. The win earned owner 
Marco Thoroughbred Corp. $120,000. 
</P>
<P>
	Roza Robata, ridden by Robby Albarado, paid $4.80 and $4.20,  
while Castle Blaze returned $12.40. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
