<HEADLINE> Holdsclaw Named WNBA's Top Rookie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Chamique Holdsclaw of the Washington Mystics  
was voted WNBA Rookie of the Year, getting 48 of a possible 51 
votes in results announced today. 
</P>
<P>
	Holdsclaw, the No. 1 pick in the May draft, averaged 16.9 points  
and 7.9 rebounds and helped the Mystics to a 12-20 record, a major 
improvement from 3-27 in 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-2 Holdsclaw was a two-time WNBA Player of the Week  
and started for the East team in the WNBA All-Star game in July. 
</P>
<P>
	One vote each from a panel of sportwriters and broadcasters went  
to Detroit's Dominique Canty, Orlando's Nykesha Sales and New 
York's Tamika Whitmore. 
</P>
<P>
	Holdsclaw said that while she was honored to receive the award,  
she missed her No. 1 goal: making the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
	She looked for greater progress next season.  
</P>
<P>
	``We won four times as many games, and with the draft,  
hopefully, we'll acquire some better players,'' she told a news 
conference. ``We'll make some trades here and there and maybe have 
a better team next year.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
