<HEADLINE> Springinthecountry Wins at Calder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Springinthecountry rallied for a 2 1/4-length victory  
over Sejm's Lunar Star in the $50,000 Convenience Stakes for 
3-year-old fillies at Calder Race Course on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Grand Veranda, the favorite, was third in the field of eight.  
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Abdiel Toribio, Springinthecountry covered 1 1-16  
miles on the turf in 1:43 and paid $8.40, $3.40 and $3. Sejm's 
Lunar Star returned $2.80 and $2.60, while Grand Veranda was $2.80 
to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Miss Glitterman, despite bearing out in the run to the first  
turn, opened a five-length lead and still was in front by three 
lengths at the five-eighths pole with Sejm's Lunar Star seventh and 
Springinthecountry last. 
</P>
<P>
	On the far turn, Miss Glitterman faded and Grand Veranda and  
Christie Light fought for the lead. Beauty Sweet rallied on the 
outside and Springinthecountry looked for room on the inside. 
</P>
<P>
	Grand Veranda, on the hedge, took a lengthy lead at the eighth  
pole with Beauty Sweet moving into second. Springinthecountry drove 
between them at the sixteenth pole and drew out. Sejm's Lunar Star 
closed fast to be second by a neck over Grand Veranda. 
</P>
<P>
	Springinthecountry is a Florida-bred by Country Pine owned by  
Ruth Goldman. She has won three of 10 starts and has finished in 
the money eight times, earning $67,835. 
</P>
<P>
	Last June 18 she was beaten in a $20,000 claiming race. The  
Convenience was her first appearance in a stakes. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
