<HEADLINE>  Tough Road for Buckeyes Football </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Ohio State's players are trying not  
to look at their problems getting to the Kickoff Classic as a bad 
omen. 
</P>
<P>
	``Everything's been bad so far,'' linebacker Na'il Diggs said.  
``Hopefully, it'll get better as the weekend goes on.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But so far, the Big Apple has been rotten for the Buckeyes.  
</P>
<P>
	They waited for 90 minutes to depart Columbus on Friday and only  
were permitted to leave after they left behind all of their baggage 
because the plane couldn't take the weight. 
</P>
<P>
	And that came after it became public that two of their top  
