<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clash 2, MetroStars 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Ronald Cerritos' goal with 23 seconds  
left forced a shootout and John Doyle scored the winning goal in 
the tiebreaker as the San Jose Clash beat the New York-New Jersey 
MetroStars 2-1 Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Eddie Lewis, Dario Brose and Alejandro Sequeira also scored in  
the shootout for the Clash (14-10). 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars (5-21) lost their 11th consecutive game.  
</P>
<P>
	Dallas held a 1-0 lead for most of the game, following Billy  
Walsh's goal in the ninth minute. But with the Clash pushing 
forward in the final minute, Cerritos took a shot from the middle 
of the penalty arc and beat goalkeeper Tim Howard just inside the 
left post. 
</P>
<P>
	In the shootout, the MetroStars took leads of 1-0, 2-1 and 3-2  
on goals by Petter Villegas, Miles Joseph and Ramiro Carrales. But 
Lewis, Brose and Sequeira countered, Clash goalkeeper Joe Cannon 
stopped Mark Semioli's attempt in the seventh round, and Doyle then 
made the game-winner. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
