<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Five Dead in Domestic Dispute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Five people were found fatally shot late  
Friday in what investigators suspect was a murder-suicide sparked 
by a domestic dispute. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers received a report of gunfire about 8:30 p.m. and  
arrived to find two women and three men dead in a Koreatown 
apartment, Lt. Sharyn Buck said. The women were believed to be in 
their 20s, but the men's ages were unknown. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're pretty sure it's a murder-suicide,'' she said. ``There  
are witnesses saying that the wife and husband were having a 
dispute. She had come back today -- apparently had moved out.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Buck said investigators believe the shooter is among the dead,  
but was unsure of who it was. 
</P>
<P>
	Edith Arreola, a 15-year-old who lived in a neighboring  
apartment complex, said she was watching television when she heard 
the gunshots. 
</P>
<P>
	``I heard screaming and then they shoot, like, 20, 21, 23,  
shots, and the lady was screaming 'help','' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	Koreatown is a working class, ethnically mixed community located  
about 4 miles west of downtown. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
