<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Saints' Quarterback Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Billy Joe Hobert, expected to be the New  
Orleans Saints' starting quarterback this season, had to leave the 
exhibition game against the Green Bay Packers Saturday night after 
a helmet blow to his right side cracked a rib. 
</P>
<P>
	Hobert spent last season on injured reserve after rupturing his  
Achilles' tendon in the first game of the year. He missed the first 
two exhibition games this year -- because of a groin pull before the 
first and the death of his sister before the second. 
</P>
<P>
	Hobert stayed in Saturday's game for most of the first half,  
despite the injury. He was 10-of-15 for 179 yards and two 
touchdowns, a 12-yarder and a 58-yarder. 
</P>
<P>
	Hobert was sacked three times, but said the injury occurred when  
a player's helmet hit him during a pass play. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
